Plugins and Gems used by this app:

Ruby 1.8.6
RubyGems 0.9.5
Rails 2.0.2

Gems
	ruby-openid
	activemerchant
	capistrano
	capistrano-ext
	railsmachine
	rubyworks-ec2
	fastercsv
	mocha (for unit testing active_merchant)
	money
	google_geocode


Restful Auth Plugin
	script/plugin install http://svn.eastmedia.com/svn/bantay/plugins/trunk/restful_open_id_authentication

ActiveMerchant
	script/plugin install http://activemerchant.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/active_merchant

RSpec
	script/plugin install -x http://rspec.rubyforge.org/svn/tags/CURRENT/rspec
	script/plugin install -x http://rspec.rubyforge.org/svn/tags/CURRENT/rspec_on_rails
	
Rubyworks
  Download http://www.nutrun.com/rwec2/releases/rubyworks-ec2-0.1.3.gem
  gem i [path-to-file]/rubyworks-ec2-0.1.3.gem
  More about using Rubyworks and what it means for EC2
  http://nutrun.com/weblog/rubyworks-production-stack-on-amazon-ec2/
	
  
EC2 Command Line Tools (Java Tools to manage EC2 instance from terminal)
  http://developer.amazonwebservices.com/connect/entry.jspa?externalID=351&categoryID=88
  More about EC2 
  http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/2007-08-29/GettingStartedGuide/
  

Environment Variables
  export JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/Home (default mac installation for Java 1.5)
  export EC2_PRIVATE_KEY=~/.ec2/pk-YMC4ZT7XIPO2GR3KMW6FE33RBC4KNCFH.pem (obtain key from Chris)
  export EC2_CERT=~/.ec2/cert-YMC4ZT7XIPO2GR3KMW6FE33RBC4KNCFH.pem (obtain cert from Chris)
  export EC2_HOME=~/ec2-api-tools-1.2-13740 (location of EC2 Tools)
  export PATH=$PATH:$EC2_HOME/bin (so java can find the tools)

MySQL
	gem install mysql -- --with-mysql-config=/usr/bin/mysql_config

